It's those &quot;other things&quot; that make the high end guilds the best. However, to ruin something that players have spent hours of time getting to just because the devs &quot;thought&quot; something was being done wrong or illegal? Gimme a fuckin break. Since when have we been guilty before proven innocent. <br>
<br>
There is simply no conceivable excuse for either the GMs or Devs to pop into a zone and break an encounter if they don't know all the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>FACTS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
Facts: (fakt) n. 1. that which actually exists; reality; truth. 2 something know to exist or to have happened. <br>
Until the facts are known, there should be no punishment of any kind dealt, period. <br>
<br>
There simply is no way to justify the actions of Sony on this, none. <br>
